<figure id="fig-ch28_00_01" class="splash"><div data-type="title">Ovulation </div><figcaption>Following a surge of luteinizing hormone (LH), an oocyte (immature egg cell) will be released into the uterine tube, where it will then be available to be fertilized by a male&#8217;s sperm. Ovulation marks the end of the follicular phase of the ovarian cycle and the start of the luteal phase.
</figcaption><span data-type="media" id="fs-id2179752" data-alt="This photo shows an oocyte.">
